2016 WW53 Bakerville/SKX-D BKC Release Announcement (BKC #6)

\n \n \n

DEG Platform Integration Team

\n \n
\n

The DEG platform Integration team announces the release of 2016 WW53 Bakerville/SKX-D BKC release package for Intel internal use. The release is based on OS of\n \n Linux/\n \n VMWare/\n \n Windows\n server. The auto-installer packages are available in the Artifactory server (both SH site and OR site). Any questions please contact Bei, Ling.

HW\nrework:

    \n
  • No HW rework\n need for Yuba City fab3 board.
    • \n
  • jumper\n setting refers to this link.
    • \n

 

Work around:

    \n
  • Secure Boot\n only can run in UEFI mode, so if we want secure boot can work and let bios\n load UEFI Oprom, we need Disable\n this option. 
    • \n

EDKII Menu -> Boot\nOptions -> EFI INT10 workaround

    \n
  • When you flash onboard Aspeed BMC, in order to\n detect onboard dTPM in AC cycle, you need run below IPMI command in UEFI\n Shell:
    • \n

#cmdtool  20 C0 3f 07

InformationQuick Guide
BKC Artifactory Access

Link (SH server): https://ubit-artifactory-sh.intel.com

Link (OR server): https://ubit-artifactory-or.intel.com

Steps for applying the permission:

  • Go to EAM website:http://eam.intel.com/EAMWeb/default.aspx
  • Click on "Add or Remove access"
  • Navigate to:"Enterprise Applications - DevTools - DEG_Purley"
  • Apply for the "Project viewer" role
  • Use your windows credentials for authentication

BKC One Stop Shop

Link: https://dcg-oss.intel.com

Steps for applying the permission:

  • Go to EAM website: http://eam.intel.com/EAMWeb/default.aspx
  • Click on "Add or Remove access"
  • Navigate to:"Enterprise Applications - CI Automation u2013 One Stop Shop (OSS) u2013 BKC u2013 Purley"
  • Apply for the "User" or "Ingredient Owner" role
  • Use your windows credentials for authentication

Contact Person: Bei, Ling
